sta-article__url-stepper"><span class="kasta-breadcrumbs"><span class="kasta-breadcrumbs__path"><a class="" href="/">Home / </a><a aria-current="page" class="active" href="/blog">Blog / </a></span><span class="kasta-breadcrumbs__tail">How to Receive Bitcoin: A Detailed Guide</span></span></div><div class="kasta-article__date-reading"><span>July 15, 2022</span><span class="circle"></span><span>4 min read</span></div><h1 class="kasta-article__name">How to Receive Bitcoin: A Detailed Guide</h1><p>Kasta is a simple and easy-to-use crypto payment app, even for those who aren’t generally techy like our grandparents. It allows you to instantly<a href="/"> send crypto</a> and receive them using just a QR code or a phone number.</p><p>If you’re a first time Kasta user and you want to know how to receive Bitcoin payments in the app, we’ve got all the details you may need in this blog post.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">What is the Kasta App? </p><p>The Kasta app allows instant cross-border crypto payments and helps people conveniently transition into a crypto-based economy by simplifying the end-to-end process of sending and receiving crypto to and from another user. Unlike other wallets or payment platforms, with Kasta, you don’t have to deal with copying and pasting long wallet addresses, memo IDs, or network types. All you need is a verified Kasta account, and the QR code or phone number of the other user to get started.</p><p>Note: The Kasta app’s first version only accepts cryptocurrencies, but the team is already working on the second version of the app, which will also accept fiat currencies such as the US Dollar and Euro.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Who Can Open a Kasta Account? </p><p>Only users 18 years and above who can form a binding contract under applicable laws in their country, and those who can provide identification documents and proof of address can open a Kasta account.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">How to Receive Bitcoin: A Step-by-Step Guide </p><section class="kasta-article__guide"><p>Here’s the end to end process of receiving Bitcoin in the Kasta app:</p><ol><li><span>1. Sign up for a Kasta account.</span><div class="kasta-article__guide__wrapper-lazy-image"><div class="kasta-image kasta-article__guide__img" style="padding-bottom: 67.2963%;"></div></div><ol><li>Download the Kasta app from the Play Store or App Store.</li><li>Open the app and sign up using your name, home address, email address, and phone number.</li><li>Set up your pin code. Be sure no one else knows it for your protection.</li><li>Complete the Know Your Customer (KYC) verification, a part of a due diligence process that aims to prevent money laundering, fraud, corruption, and terrorist financing, by providing your valid ID and proof of residency.</li></ol></li><li><span>2. Receive Bitcoin into your account.</span><div class="kasta-article__guide__wrapper-lazy-image"><div class="kasta-image kasta-article__guide__img" style="padding-bottom: 35.9526%;"></div></div><ol><li>Log in to your Kasta account.</li><li>Enter the verification code sent to your mobile number.</li><li>On the dashboard, click the “Receive” button.</li><li>Copy your QR code.</li><li>Send the QR code to the sender, or you can also give the phone number you used to sign up on Kasta.</li><li>Wait for the other user to send the payment.</li></ol></li></ol></section><p>Note: If the other user wants to send the payment in another currency but you prefer to receive it in Bitcoin, you can enable the Easy Swap Engine and set it up to automatically receive the payment in Bitcoin.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">How to Automatically Receive Payments in Bitcoin Using the Easy Swap Engine </p><section><div class="kasta-article__wrapper-lazy-image"><div class="kasta-image kasta-article__wrapper-lazy-image__img-zoom" style="padding-bottom: 31.1506%;"></div></div></section><ol class=""><li>Click the settings icon on the upper right part of the Kasta app dashboard.</li><li>Click “Easy Swap” from the drawer.</li><li>Tick the “Enable Easy Swap” button.</li><li>On the first dropdown, choose the currency that when received, you want to convert to Bitcoin. You may also select all currencies.</li><li>Choose Bitcoin on the second dropdown.</li></ol><p class="kasta-article__text">How Much are Crypto Transfer Fees? </p><p>The awesome news is that it’s free to receive payments in the same currency in the Kasta app. This means you won’t get deducted when the other user sends you Bitcoin and you also receive it in Bitcoin. However, when the Easy Swap Engine converts a payment into your preferred currency, you have to pay a minimal conversion fee. The fee will be charged in the source currency, which means if you send Bitcoin and they receive it in Ethereum, the fee will be charged in Bitcoin.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">How Long Does it Take to Receive Bitcoin? </p><p>The Kasta app has an internal virtual ledger that makes it possible to send and receive crypto instantly – no more waiting for hours, several days, or even over a week. It works as a chain-agnostic source of truth and is backed by our auto-balancing liquidity pools. Therefore, you can expect to receive your Bitcoin in just a few seconds after the other user has finished sending the payment.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">How to Receive Bitcoin From Your External Wallet </p><p>Here’s how you can receive Bitcoin from an external wallet:</p><ol class=""><li>Log in to your Kasta account.</li><li>Enter the verification code sent to your mobile number.</li><li>Click the “Add Funds” button on the dashboard.</li><li>Click “Deposit from a wallet.”</li><li>Choose Bitcoin.</li><li>Copy your Kasta wallet address.</li><li>On your external wallet, choose to withdraw Bitcoin, paste your Bitcoin wallet address from Kasta, and proceed with the transaction.</li><li>And poof! Bitcoin received in your Kasta account!</li></ol><p class="kasta-article__text">Will I Be Able to View My Transaction History in the App? </p><p>Of course! Please click the lower rightmost icon on the dashboard to view your transaction history, including the assets you’ve sent, received, deposited, withdrawn, and swapped. You will also be able to see your rewards here.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Which Cryptocurrencies are Accepted on the App? </p><p>The first version of the Kasta app only accepts four cryptocurrencies which include Bitcoin, Ethereum, Tether, and the KASTA token. The second version of the app is in the works, which will also accept fiat currencies.</p><p>If you’re interested to know <a href="/token"> what is the KASTA token</a>, it’s the official cryptocurrency of the Kasta app. You can use it to pay for conversion fees in the app, as a payment method for goods, dining, and services, or as a source of passive income through<a href="https://medium.com/@kasta_app/stake-kasta-on-bybit-now-e20580b4b52"> staking</a>.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Is it Safe to Use the Kasta App? </p><p>Yes. Kasta has two-factor authentication. Users won’t be able to log in unless they verify their phone numbers using a verification code, and they cannot complete a transaction without correctly entering their pin code. In addition, Kasta follows anti-money laundering (AML) guidelines and KYC processes to verify individuals and protect users against money laundering, fraud, and other illegal activities.</p><p class="kasta-article__text">Do You Have Customer Support? </p><p>Yes. The Kasta app has live chat support, so please feel free to reach out if you have questions or concerns with your transactions.</p><div class="kasta-article__recomended-by-kasta"><p>Recommended by Kasta</p><a aria-current="page" class="recomended-cards__link active" href="/blog">Check more posts</a></div></div><div class="kasta-cookie-banner"><div class="kasta-cookie-banner__text">We use cookies to enhance your experience and analyze our site usage. Please see our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for